1 I watched this film without knowing anything about it whatsoever and found it similar thematically to Billy Elliott ( 2000 ) . Both films are based around a troubled father / son relationship . In both films , the son does not want to follow his father down the mines and dreams of a better life away from their home town . Both sons face derision by their classmates and both have a strong female role model who teaches them.<br /><br />The major difference that I found between the films was that October Sky was an infinitely more interesting and touching film . Laura Dern puts in a moving performance and Chris Cooper plays the disapproving father very well as he went on to do in American Beauty ( 1999 ) . Joe Johnston surprised me with his subtle directing , very different from his other directorial features such as Jumanji ( 1995 ) and Jurassic Park III ( 2001).<br /><br / >
