1 Purple Rain is a great film if you are a 40-something music lover who partied to Prince music in the 1980s . The story is a much - used formula : Rising musical talent must overcome personal and professional hurdles to find his audience and self - respect . Prince is a bad actor , but his performance , especially of Purple Rain / I Would Die 4 U make it worth sitting through the film . He is himself and as a showman , as powerful on stage as Mick Jagger or Michael Jackson , circa Thriller . Apollonia Kotero , a former Prince protégé , is beautiful and shows some acting talent and chemistry with Prince , but her script does n't let her far . Morris Day and other supporting actors provide comedic elements .
