1 Fifteen years later and Paris Is Burning is still aflame . This is a classic in black gay films , right up there with the other honorary black gay films , The Color Purple and Mahoganoy . This seminal work captures underground and underclass ( i.e."underserved ) black and Latin gay culture and community like no other work before or since , including all the sentimental Harlem Rennaissance gay retrospectives and renderings . They 're good , but this is the best ( dare I say the only " real " ) film you 'll find on the subject . It 's Relentlessy Cunty ( the classic house music invention)comes to Hollywood , non - stop , hilarious camp ( like only we do it ) and dead - on social critique . All this by a white female director ( who obviously must have been a Sister Gurl or Mizz Thing in a former life . ) I could go on , but I think you get the point by now : I love this movie !
