1 It is hard to describe Bug in words , it is one of those films that truly has to be seen to be understood . It follows a narrative that is more fluid and interesting than anything I have seen lately in a Hollywood release . As its characters react to the chain of events in different ways , and as the events dictate different paths for the characters to follow , the audience is merely an observer . The almost Proustian narrative flow of thought to thought , the very spontaneity in the script will have you glued to the screen , waiting anxiously to see how it all works out in the end . And as far as the thematic elements ... there is a particular sequence in the film that goes from melancholy , to bright and beautiful , and then to tragic , all within the span of about a minute . And it works.<br /><br />This movie is pure magic . It reminds one why independent film is perhaps the brightest star the film industry currently has . Perhaps with more movies of Bug 's quality , people will start to take notice .
