1 ' How to Lose Friends and Alienate People ' is an entertaining , if loose , adaptation of Toby Young 's memoir of the same name . It 's also a great title for helping to fill up the line requirement in IMDb reviews ! The basic gist is the same as the book with certain incidents dramatised , but a romantic plot is added and the ending is certainly Hollywoodised . Simon Pegg , despite playing an essentially irritating person , is his usual likable and funny self and pretty much carries the film . Strange to think only a few years ago he was just a TV sitcom guy and now he 's rubbing shoulders with Hollywood names . There 's a good supporting cast and it 's an amusing , easy watch - kind of a male ' Ugly Betty ' , but funnier .
